					<td background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/trick.jpg" width="100%" valign="top">


<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">

		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Mage Guide</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:lamutian@netzero.net">Chuan Q. Ho</a> | 
		            8/25/1999 6:31:44 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">High elf and gnome magicians have access to the best early hunting areas in the game. That's why I like them so much. Erudites and Dark elves have AWFUL newbie zones in comparison to Gnomes and High elves. Steamfont isn't great but Greater Faydark is only a short walk away from Ak Anon for Gnomes.<BR>
<BR>
First of all, I will tell you where I hunted with my High Elf magician through 16th level. These hunting grounds all give awesome xp and most of them give GREAT loot.<BR>
<BR>
Levels 1 through 4 will be spent in Greater Faydark. At level 1, you should hunt wasps and skeletons, especially if you see one with a weapon. Wasps can have great loot if you're lucky. Some carry royal jellies, which sell for approx 4 silver. On VERY rare occasions, you can find a poison sac on a wasp. These things sell for more than 3 gold! Once you hit level two, start killing orc pawns, especially ones with hatchets. You should start to suck up to the Rangers of Kelethin and a good way to do that is to give Dill in the Rangers Guild orc hatchets. <BR>
<BR>
Once you hit level 4, immediately buy Burn and Elementalkin: Earth from your local Magician Guild. Then head to the Pixie Tower in Lesser Faydark. Once you zone into Lesser Faydark from Greater Faydark, go straight on the road and take your first right. Follow the path and ignore the right turn. It's a long walk but you'll eventually wind up near the Pixie Tower at the end of the path. Hunt pixie tricksters and pixie pranksters with your pet until 8th level. These 4 levels should come up so fast you'll be amazed. The pixies also have EXCELLENT loot and the best way to maximize their loot is to turn in all of your pixie dust to Ran in the Ranger's Guild. If you can, get bound right inside the Ranger's Guild next to Merchant Tuluvdar because you will be extremely encumbered from all the loot you get from the pixies. Always sell in the Ranger's Guild from now on because they will love you for doing the pixie dust quest millions of times. At level 4, I made anywhere from 4 to 9 plat each trip to the Pixie Tower. <BR>
<BR>
Ok, once you hit 8th level, head to Steamfont. There is a little area in this zone overflowing with approx 10th level prey. Yes, you can easily solo yellows here because they are all weak. Make sure you have Shock of Blades and an earth elemental though. Your chances of survival and success depends on your pet. If you get a level 7 pet, try again to get a better one. Anyway, the area I am talking about is the one in front and behind the entrance to the minotaur cave, right where the Hero spawns. It does sound dangerous as the Hero is a level 40 aggressive. However, you can easily avoid him if you know where to meditate. Here, hunt decaying skeletons(there are approx lvl 10 decaying skeletons here), skeletons, gnome skeletons, harpies, drakes, and earth elementals. Watch out for the rats, they are everywhere and they have a tendency to jump you when you're pet is occupied with something else. Watch out for all wandering aggressives like elementals, rats, and minotaur slavers. Notice that the Hero is not a wandering aggressive. He follows a very strange route that is pretty out of the way. Minotaur slavers spawn very rarely out here and never has an axe so they aren't too dangerous. The skeletons make a kind of ring, at the center of which are three geysers. Resting by the geysers is extremely safe as no wandering aggressives come there and the Hero's Route is far enough away so he will not attack you. There are 5 skeletons spawn points that you can camp here but you only need two. They do not wander and have low aggression but they will attack if you come too close. Hunt here in the manner described until you hit 12th level. Then you will move on to Lavastorm.<BR>
<BR>
Dark Elves have easy access to this area but the rest of us do not. Erudites have the toughest time of all. The only major problem for Gnomes and High Elves are the guards in Nektulos Forest. But with invisibility, they are not much of a problem.<BR>
<BR>
Once you zone into Lavastorm from Nektulos Forest, follow the wall to the right until you see a huge entrance with the left door fallen down. That is the entrance to Najena and it is the safest spot to hunt in Lavastorm. The tunnel leading to Najena is very safe until someone trains an 18th level fire elemental to the Najena zone. Then you should either run out of the tunnel and far from the doors so the fire elemental would not attack you or zone into Najena. Personally I prefer the first method but if its already attacking you then only the second method will save you.<BR>
<BR>
At this level, you will still be using Shock of Blades. You will be tempted to hunt fire elementals using Ward Summoned but believe me, they are not worth hunting. They are the third toughest monster after the lava crawlers and fire imps and have nothing for loot most of the time. If you're lucky, you will get a bloodstone from one of them but drakes, which are EXTREMELY easy, have much better loot. I know some Dark Elves at level 8 who hunt the drakes here but you don't survive long at level 8 because of the fire imps and fire elementals. Hunting here from level 12 to 16 will make you a rich magician. I made around 30 plat each trip to Lavastorm. Make sure you get dimensional pockets so you can keep the small blocks of ore you get from the rock dervishes. All the loot you find here are worth more than 2 gold except for the fire drakes' scales, which are worth approx 4 silver. <BR>
<BR>
Make sure when you are hunting in Steamfont and Lavastorm, that you do your best to help the other people who hunt here. The only way to survive in thse two places is to help each other. Trust me, you will need help a lot and if you don't help others, they won't help you.<BR>
<BR>
I hope my advice helps you reach level 16th with ease and a lot of money. I know I did.
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
				<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td></tr>
